# Styling Conventions

## Design Tokens

All colors, fonts, and shadows are defined as CSS custom properties in `:root` in `src/index.css`. Never hardcode values -- always use `var(--token)`.

```css
:root {
  --gold-primary: #C9A227;
  --gold-light: #D4AF37;
  --gold-dark: #8B7355;
  --burgundy: #722F37;
  --white: #FFFFFF;
  --cream: #FAF8F0;
  --black: #1A1A1A;
  --charcoal: #2C2C2C;
  --gray: #6B6B6B;
  --gray-light: #A0A0A0;
  --font-display: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
  --font-body: 'Montserrat', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
  --shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  --shadow-gold: 0 4px 30px rgba(201, 162, 39, 0.3);
}
```

## Single Stylesheet

All styles live in `src/index.css`. Do not create per-component CSS files.

## BEM Naming

```css
.block {}
.block__element {}
.block--modifier {}
```

## Modern CSS Practices

- Use `clamp()` for fluid typography
- Use `aspect-ratio` instead of padding hacks
- Use `min-height: 100svh` for mobile-safe viewport heights
- Use logical properties (`margin-inline`, `padding-block`) where appropriate
- Use `:focus-visible` for keyboard-only focus rings
- Use `@media (hover: hover)` to scope hover effects to pointer devices
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`

## Animations

- Only animate `transform` and `opacity` (GPU-composited)
- Standard transition: `transition: property 0.3s ease`
- Always include the `prefers-reduced-motion` override at the end of `index.css`

## Responsive

- Mobile-first: write base styles for 320px+, add `@media (min-width: 768px)` for desktop
- Breakpoint: 768px (matches `useIsMobile` hook)
- Touch targets: minimum 48px height on mobile
- Use `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)` on fixed bottom elements

## Slider Containers

Hero: 2:3 portrait ratio (70x105 Three.js units, 280x420px CSS)
Gallery: 3:4 portrait ratio (120x160 Three.js units, 300x400px CSS)

## Mobile Fallback

On mobile, Three.js sliders are replaced by `ImageCrossfade` component with CSS transitions. See the `css-modern-patterns` skill for crossfade implementation.
